        <Info>
            <Description>The Glasgow Coma Scale (GCS) is a standardized instrument for assessing the level of consciousness. It evaluates three aspects of responsiveness: eye opening, motor response, verbal response. From the National Institute of Neurological Disorders and Stroke (NIH / NINDS).</Description>
            <Contact>
                <Name />
                <Institution>American College of Radiology</Institution>
            </Contact>
        </Info>
